  "response_text": "The commercial opens in black and white on a pale, compact rotary telephone resting on a small round table. The phone has a low, rounded base, a handset lying across the top, a circular dial set into the center, and a coiled cord trailing off to the left. Behind it sits an ornate decorative object, giving the tabletop a formal living-room feel. Script lettering appears across the lower part of the image reading “The Princess,” identifying the product.\n\nA smiling young adult woman then appears in a furnished living room beside the same telephone. She has shoulder-length dark wavy hair, wears a fitted dress with a light neckline and a short pearl necklace, and faces forward as a presenter. The room has curtains behind her, an upholstered chair in the background, and a small round table at her side holding the Princess Phone and a decorative lamp or vase-like object. She smiles warmly, then looks down toward the phone and places her hand near it as if introducing and demonstrating it. The phone sits neatly on the tabletop, its small size emphasized by how little space it takes beside the other furnishings.\n\nThe setting changes to a kitchen. A woman in a light short-sleeved blouse and patterned apron stands behind a counter with a large mixing bowl and utensils in front of her. Cabinets line the back wall, and pots and kitchen items hang or sit around the workspace. The Princess Phone is on a counter or shelf to her right. While working at the bowl, she reaches across to the phone, lifts it, and moves it closer to her on the counter. She sets the base down near the mixing bowl, showing it as light and portable within the kitchen. She then lifts the receiver to her ear and continues handling items on the counter with her other hand, combining a phone call with food preparation. The coiled cord stretches from the receiver to the small base.\n\nThe scene moves to a living room or den with a middle-aged man seated in an armchair. He wears a dark jacket or cardigan over a light shirt. Around him are a low cabinet or console, shelves with books or decorative objects, a table lamp, patterned curtains, and a side table next to the chair. The Princess Phone sits on that side table within easy reach. The man leans forward toward the cabinet, then settles back into the chair with papers or a magazine on his lap. He picks up the receiver from the nearby phone and holds it to his ear while relaxing in the chair, the cord running down to the phone base on the table.\n\nA bedroom scene follows. A woman lies asleep on her side in bed, partly covered by a striped blanket or bedspread, her head resting on a striped pillow. The room is dim, and a Princess Phone sits on the bedside table just beyond her. The phone’s pale shape is visible in the low light beside the bed. The image then emphasizes the phone itself: the handset lies across the top, and the dial area glows softly. As the receiver is lifted from the cradle, the circular dial becomes brighter and easier to see, showing the lighted feature of the phone for use in the dark.\n\nThe presenter returns in the living room beside the Princess Phone. She smiles toward the viewer, then glances down at the phone and gestures over it with an open hand, drawing attention to its compact, rounded shape and central rotary dial. She rests her hand near the phone as she continues presenting it. The final images return to the close view of the Princess Phone alone on the round table. At the bottom of the screen, white text appears: “Order yours at your Telephone Company Business Office,” accompanied by a small Bell System-style logo. The pale telephone remains centered above the ordering message, with its coiled cord to the left and its handset neatly in place.",
